[{"id":"VR803357","type":"mcq","stimulusHtml":"<p class=\"stem_paragraph\">A spherical conductor of radius <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"r\"><math alttext=\"r\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mi>r</mi></math></span></span> is given a charge <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"positive Q\"><math alttext=\"positive Q\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mstyle displaystyle=\"true\"><mo>+</mo><mi>Q</mi></mstyle></math></span></span>. What is the electric potential inside the spherical conductor at half of its radius and why?</p>\n","rubricRef":"VR803357_rubric","choicesHtml":["<p class=\"choice_paragraph\">Zero, because there canâ€™t be an electric field inside a conductor.</p>","<p class=\"choice_paragraph\"><span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"the fraction with numerator k Q, and denominator 4 r\"><math alttext=\"the fraction with numerator k Q, and denominator 4 r\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mstyle displaystyle=\"true\"><mfrac><mrow><mi>k</mi><mi>Q</mi></mrow><mrow><mn>4</mn><mi>r</mi></mrow></mfrac></mstyle></math></span></span>, because half the radius contains an eighth of the charge.</p>","<p class=\"choice_paragraph\"><span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"the fraction with numerator k Q, and denominator r\"><math alttext=\"the fraction with numerator k Q, and denominator r\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mstyle displaystyle=\"true\"><mfrac><mrow><mi>k</mi><mi>Q</mi></mrow><mi>r</mi></mfrac></mstyle></math></span></span>, because the conductor is spherical, and it has the same potential everywhere.</p>","<p class=\"choice_paragraph\"><span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"the fraction with numerator 2 k Q, and denominator r\"><math alttext=\"the fraction with numerator 2 k Q, and denominator r\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mstyle displaystyle=\"true\"><mfrac><mrow><mn>2</mn><mi>k</mi><mi>Q</mi></mrow><mi>r</mi></mfrac></mstyle></math></span></span>, because only the charge inside half the radius determines the electric potential.</p>"],"answer":2}]